Karen Meyer the MMC for Community Safety in Tshwane explained why the city wants to increase its CCTV camera surveillance. Courtesy #DStv403 TSHWANE - The capital city has big plans to enhance safety and security. Tshwane wants to increase the number of CCTV cameras and introduce a scout programme where residents become more involved in policing their communities. READ: Police turn to CCTV footage in homeless killings "Security and safety issue still lies corely with SAPS however as a city we have an obligation to play our part as well," said MMC for Community Safety, Karen Meyer. Meyer said technology has to be utilised to improve community safety. Collaboration and partnerships with private and public resources are critical for the safety and security of any city, Meyer added.